  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Superb Hospital with amazing staff&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Peter Mahony&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was apprehensive about needing a complete knee replacement, but typical pain and walking difficulties made the procedure inevitable.
The CV-19 pandemic limited NHS hospital availability. However, from a selection of Hospitals offered, I elected to be treated at Tees Valley Hospital and referred to Mr James Webb in September 2020. An extremely experienced knee surgeon, he recommended a complete knee replacement.
My procedure was planned for mid-December and after the necessary CV-19 test I was admitted on December 12th. Within a few hours of admission I was prepped for surgery and had a spinal anaesthetic. 
The whole operation was professionally managed by the Theatre Team. Reassurance and keeping me informed was a priority of the Anaesthetist whilst doing Observations. I was also given some good advice for distraction during the operation and had music playing via my mobile and headphones.
The post-op nursing staff ensured my recovery was well managed and again plenty of reassurance and the occasional apology for cold water spraying (torso reaction test), as I recovered from the anaesthetic. On returning to the Ward the nursing team continued the excellent care that was clearly standard procedure to them.  
After resting overnight and enjoying some superb food, the Physio Team encouraged me to take my first few steps. No problem, everything felt good and although I was still under medication they were delighted with my progress. No need for the walking frame, skipped that stage, two sticks and strict instructions of do's and don'ts. 
Just over 24 hours later from admission it was time to say goodbye to the wonderful staff. Next, I was travelling home, exercise list in one hand and medication in the other. 
Its Christmas Day as I write, nearly two weeks on from the operation and I am so pleased with the results. Swelling subsiding, bruising faded and I'm cutting back on pain relief. Best present I could have received and so grateful to the Teams who played each of their parts brilliantly. Thankyou all, I will be back to be discharged in the New Year.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
